Local disaster relief authorities on Tuesday revised the death toll from the tropical storm in the Philippines over the weekend to 20, adding further verification is still needed. Six other people were injured, over 139,000 people were affected, and more than 17,000 were relocated. (Cover: Coast guards and police evacuate a resident from a flooded area in Abuyog town, Leyte Province, southern Philippines, April 11, 2022. /CFP)